              In 2026, you can call GPT-4o-class, Llama 3.x, DeepSeek V3, and Gemini 2.5 Pro without a credit card, from a single API key. This guide catalogs <strong>14 free AI API platforms</strong> — 6 international, 5 China-based, and 3 aggregators — then picks the <strong>3 best for daily use</strong> based on signup friction, model quality, rate limits, and ecosystem fit.
            </p>
          </header>

          <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">

            <h2>Why "Free AI API" Is a Different Question in 2026 Than It Was in 2024</h2>
            <p>Two years ago, "free AI API" meant one of two things: a token-limited OpenAI trial credit, or a slow HuggingFace Spaces demo. In 2026, the landscape has shifted — and most of the shift happened in 2025 when <strong>aggregator platforms</strong> like <a href="/tutorials/freemodel-api-review/">FreeModel</a> and <a href="/tutorials/openrouter-fusion-api-2026/">OpenRouter</a> collapsed 10+ provider relationships into a single endpoint.</p>
            <p>Today there are three distinct patterns of "free" in the AI API market:</p>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>No-credit-card rate-limited tier:</strong> Google AI Studio (Gemini), Groq, Mistral, Cohere, Cloudflare Workers AI, HuggingFace Inference API. You sign up with an email, get an API key, and the platform gives you a fixed quota per minute or per day. No card, no expiry — but rate-limited.</li>
              <li><strong>Free credits on signup that expire:</strong> OpenRouter signup bonus, Mistral trial ($5), Cohere trial key, most cloud-provider free credits. You get $5-50 of credit at signup, valid for 30-90 days. No card needed, but the credits run out.</li>
              <li><strong>Free model access via aggregator:</strong> <a href="https://freemodel.dev/invite/FRE-7a3b6220" target="_blank" rel="sponsored noopener">FreeModel</a> (free credits on signup, OpenAI/Anthropic compatible endpoint, auto-routing across models), OpenRouter's `:free` model tier (13+ models marked `:free` at time of writing). One key, many models — and the free quota is renewed monthly or refills per-request.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>This article catalogs all three patterns across 14 platforms, then picks the 3 winners by daily-use scenario. If you've ever asked "where should I sign up for a free AI API today?" — keep reading.</p>

            <h2>International Platforms — Free API With No Credit Card</h2>
            <p>These six platforms serve a global audience and accept signup with just an email or Google account. No credit card required for any of them.</p>

            <h3>Google AI Studio (Gemini API)</h3>
            <p>Google's AI Studio gives you a free Gemini API key with no credit card. The free tier includes Gemini 2.5 Pro (1M-token context window), Gemini 2.5 Flash, Gemini 2.0 Flash, and the older 1.5 Pro/Flash models. Rate limits are 15 RPM (requests per minute) on Pro and 60 RPM on Flash — workable for individual developers and prototypes.</p>
            <p><strong>Multimodal:</strong> Vision (image input), audio input, video input all included. <strong>Free quota:</strong> No daily cap at time of writing, just rate-limited per minute. <strong>Best for:</strong> Multimodal prototypes, large-context analysis (PDFs, codebases), production-grade reliability from a major lab.</p>

            <h3>Groq</h3>
            <p>Groq runs open-source models (Llama 3.x, Mixtral, Gemma) on their custom LPU silicon — measured at 300+ tokens/sec inference latency. Free tier requires email signup, gives you access to all open-source models with rate limits around 30 RPM depending on the model.</p>
            <p><strong>Free quota:</strong> Rate-limited per model. <strong>Best for:</strong> Speed-critical applications — real-time chatbots, streaming responses, anything where "feels slow" matters.</p>

            <h3>Mistral AI (La Plateforme)</h3>
            <p>Mistral gives you a $5 free trial credit at signup with no card. Access to Mistral 7B, Mixtral 8x7B, Mistral Small, Mistral Medium, and the codestral models. EU-hosted, GDPR-friendly.</p>
            <p><strong>Free quota:</strong> $5 credit, expires after 30 days. <strong>Best for:</strong> EU users needing GDPR compliance, function calling with JSON mode, Mistral-specific features.</p>

            <h3>Cohere</h3>
            <p>Cohere's free trial API key gives access to Command R+, Command R, and the Embed model family. Trial key has rate limits but is generous enough for prototyping RAG pipelines and embedding workflows.</p>
            <p><strong>Free quota:</strong> Trial tier with rate limits. <strong>Best for:</strong> RAG applications, Embeddings (Cohere's embed models are competitive), enterprise-leaning tasks.</p>

            <h3>Cloudflare Workers AI</h3>
            <p>Run Llama, Mistral, embedding models, and image generation directly on Cloudflare's edge network. Free tier includes 10,000 neurons/day. No separate API key — your Cloudflare account token authenticates requests.</p>
            <p><strong>Free quota:</strong> 10,000 neurons/day (where 1 neuron ≈ a small text inference call). <strong>Best for:</strong> Edge deployment (low latency by running on Cloudflare's 300+ POPs), Cloudflare Workers ecosystem users.</p>

            <h3>HuggingFace Inference API</h3>
            <p>Free tier with HF token gives access to thousands of open-source models hosted on HuggingFace's infrastructure. Llama, Mistral, Qwen, Phi, DeepSeek, niche research models — all behind one inference endpoint.</p>
            <p><strong>Free quota:</strong> Rate-limited, model-dependent. <strong>Best for:</strong> Experimentation, open-source model access, niche research models not available elsewhere.</p>

            <h2>China-Based Platforms — Free API for CN Developers</h2>
            <p>For developers in mainland China, international platforms are often blocked or throttled. These five platforms offer native CN access, Chinese-language support, and (in most cases) generous free signup credits.</p>

            <h3>DeepSeek API</h3>
            <p>DeepSeek offers <a href="/tutorials/deepseek-api-review/">free signup credits</a> (typically ¥10-50 / ~$1.40-7 USD equivalent) on first account creation. Access to DeepSeek V3, R1 (reasoning), V2.5, and DeepSeek Coder models. OpenAI-compatible endpoint — drop-in replacement for any OpenAI SDK call.</p>
            <p><strong>Free quota:</strong> Signup credits + per-token pricing after. <strong>Best for:</strong> Coding tasks, math/reasoning, cost-sensitive CN deployments, R1 reasoning model.</p>

            <h3>Qwen (Alibaba Cloud DashScope)</h3>
            <p>Alibaba's Qwen family — Qwen-Turbo, Qwen-Plus, Qwen-Max, Qwen-Long (1M context) — is available via the DashScope platform. Free tier requires an Alibaba Cloud account (free signup, no card). Qwen-Long offers 1M-token context on a free tier, which is rare.</p>
            <p><strong>Free quota:</strong> Rate-limited free tier on Qwen-Turbo; signup credits for Plus/Max. <strong>Best for:</strong> Chinese language tasks, long-context analysis, multimodal (vision).</p>

            <h3>Zhipu GLM (智谱)</h3>
            <p>Zhipu's GLM family — GLM-4, GLM-4-Flash, GLM-Z1 (reasoning) — is hosted in mainland China with CN-friendly endpoints. <a href="/tutorials/zhipu-glm-4-api-review/">GLM-4-Flash</a> is free with rate limits; GLM-4 and Z1 require credits.</p>
            <p><strong>Free quota:</strong> GLM-4-Flash rate-limited free tier. <strong>Best for:</strong> Chinese NLP, agent frameworks, cost-sensitive CN deployments.</p>

            <h3>Moonshot Kimi</h3>
            <p>Moonshot's Kimi K2 and Moonshot V1 models specialize in long-context tasks (128K-256K tokens). Free tier with rate limits; CN-hosted.</p>
            <p><strong>Free quota:</strong> Rate-limited free tier. <strong>Best for:</strong> Long document analysis (Kimi's original use case), Chinese language, agent backends needing long context.</p>

            <h3>SiliconFlow (硅基流动)</h3>
            <p>SiliconFlow aggregates multiple open-source models (Qwen, GLM, Yi, DeepSeek, Llama) on a unified API. Free tier with rate limits across all models. Popular in the Chinese developer community for model variety.</p>
            <p><strong>Free quota:</strong> Rate-limited across multiple model families. <strong>Best for:</strong> Model variety, Chinese dev community, BYO model hosting.</p>

            <h2>Aggregator Platforms — One Key, Multiple Models</h2>
            <p>Aggregators changed the game in 2025. Instead of juggling 5 provider API keys, you get one endpoint that fronts multiple underlying models. Three platforms lead this category.</p>

            <h3>FreeModel</h3>
            <p><a href="https://freemodel.dev/invite/FRE-7a3b6220" target="_blank" rel="sponsored noopener">FreeModel</a> is a multi-model gateway that routes each request to the best-fit model from a pool including DeepSeek V3/R1, GLM, Qwen, MiniMax, Kimi, and Llama. The endpoint speaks both <strong>OpenAI format</strong> (`v1/chat/completions` and `v1/responses`) and <strong>Anthropic format</strong> (`v1/messages`) — meaning your existing OpenAI SDK or Claude SDK works with just a base URL change.</p>
            <p><strong>Signup:</strong> Email or Google OAuth. Free API credits land instantly on verification. No credit card required.</p>
            <p><strong>Auto-routing + fallback:</strong> If a model is throttled or unavailable, requests fall back automatically — no manual retry logic needed in your code.</p>
            <p><strong>For China developers:</strong> Direct connectivity from mainland China, no proxy required — this is one of the platform's primary differentiators.</p>

            <h3>OpenRouter (Free Models Tier)</h3>
            <p>OpenRouter catalogs 400+ models behind a single API key. The free models — marked with `:free` in the model name — currently include 13+ frontier-tier options verified July 6, 2026:</p>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>NVIDIA Nemotron 3 Ultra (free)</strong> — 1M-token context, 55B active params out of 550B (MoE), built for long-running agentic workflows</li>
              <li><strong>Poolside Laguna M.1 (free)</strong> — 739B tokens processed in the last week, frontier-tier reasoning</li>
              <li><strong>OpenAI gpt-oss-120b (free)</strong> — OpenAI's open-weight model, 120B params</li>
              <li><strong>Google Gemma 4 31B (free)</strong> — Google's open-weight multimodal</li>
              <li><strong>Cohere North Mini Code (free)</strong> — Coding-specialized</li>
              <li><strong>NVIDIA Nemotron 3 Super / Nano / Nano Omni (free)</strong> — Multiple Nemotron sizes</li>
              <li><strong>Poolside Laguna XS.2 / XS 2.1 (free)</strong> — Smaller Poolside variants</li>
            </ul>
            <p><strong>Signup:</strong> Email signup at <a href="https://openrouter.ai/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">openrouter.ai</a>; some `:free` models require the OpenRouter signup credit tier, others are no-card-required.</p>
            <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Browsing the frontier model landscape without paying for each one individually.</p>

            <h3>GitHub Models</h3>
            <p>GitHub Models offers free access to GPT-4o, Llama, Phi, Mistral, and other models via a GitHub account. No credit card. Rate limits are low (designed for CI/CD and experimentation, not production).</p>
            <p><strong>Free quota:</strong> Low RPM, designed for GitHub Actions and quick prototyping. <strong>Best for:</strong> GitHub users running CI/CD pipelines with AI, quick experimentation inside the GitHub ecosystem.</p>

